  1.1 Notes - Added a filter to tighten material determination, which fixed the knitting issue.
            - Renamed file to crafting_project.lic
            - Full execution command is now, for example ;crafting_project PRODUCE "a knit hat"
            - Added a filter for default yarn to correctly pull the 'yarn' stock, not the 'wool'
            - Cleaned up the help notes a little in LichCraftingProject
  
  This script is intended to be able to complete a crafting PROJECT needing only the recipe name
  as an argument. There is an optional material name argument, though there are no filters or
  sorters to ensure that the optional material name is of the material type needed for the recipe.
  
  1. This script utilizes [ base-recipes.yaml ] and [ base-crafting.yaml ] to...
    (a) find the [BaseRecipe] in [ base-recipes.yaml ] of matching a given name,
    (b) determine the [BaseDiscipline] in [ base-crafting.yaml ] by cross-referencing the 
        [BaseRecipe] discipline and [hometown],
    (c) create the needed [CraftingComponent] objects out of [BaseStock] and [BaseRecipePart], 
        both utilizing [ base-crafting.yaml], based on the information in the [BaseRecipe] 
        and [BaseDiscipline] for the [CraftingProject].
  
  All [CraftingComponent] objects contain...
    (a) the required recipe quantity information,
    (b) a method to determine what is currently on hand in the player's crafting container,
    (c) what is still needed, and
    (d) a method to resolve any missing components through purchase.
  
  2. The script will then PREPARE to craft by resolving the necessary CraftingComponents by...
    (a) ordering the ones with an order id, or
    (b) buying them by name.
  
  3. The script will then execute the correct lich crafting script, assembling and passing on
     the necessary arguments using a variety of CraftingProduct information.


  *NOTE* This script also has a LIST function to access the raw information from the the two
         databases:   [ base-recipes.yaml ] and [ base-crafting.yaml ]

=end

